                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/118.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-23T19:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 23, 1915—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>356. My 351, February 23, 3 p.m. The representatives of countries whose nationals
                    are exempted by the text of existing treaties as mentioned <pb facs="1102"
                        n="986" xml:id="pg_986"/> in my previous telegram are sending tonight to
                    Carranza a telegram asking for a reconsideration of the decree in so far as
                    their nationals are concerned. At the meeting it was thought advisable that when
                    you make your representations to Carranza in behalf of American interests you
                    give your support to the above mentioned representations made by them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
